<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0549 </DOCNO><TEXT>This book focuses on the military and political relations between theUS and USSR and the effects of these relations on other states. Workingfrom the controversial thesis that super-power sovereignty is being erodedand that their allies and satellites will exert greater influence onthe conduct of world affairs toward the end of this decade, the authorprovides a throughly up-to-date account of the most recent developmentsin US/USSR relations in diplomacy, defense and the international economy.</TEXT></DOC>